<?xml-stylesheet type="text/xsl" href="mathml.xsl"?><html xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml" xmlns:pref="http://www.w3.org/2002/Math/preference" pref:renderer="mathplayer-dl"><head><meta http-equiv="Content-Type" content="text/html; charset=UTF-8" /><title>gluBeginPolygon</title><meta name="generator" content="DocBook XSL Stylesheets V1.69.1" /></head><body><div class="refentry" lang="en" xml:lang="en"><a id="gluBeginPolygon"></a><div class="titlepage"></div><div class="refnamediv"><h2>Name</h2><p>gluBeginPolygon — delimit a polygon description</p></div><div class="refsynopsisdiv"><h2>C Specification</h2><div class="funcsynopsis"><p><code class="funcdef">void <b class="fsfunc">gluBeginPolygon</b>(</code>GLUtesselator* <var class="pdparam">tess</var><code>)</code>;</p></div></div><div class="refsynopsisdiv"><h2>C Specification</h2><div class="funcsynopsis"><p><code class="funcdef">void <b class="fsfunc">gluEndPolygon</b>(</code>GLUtesselator* <var class="pdparam">tess</var><code>)</code>;</p></div></div><div class="refsect1" lang="en" xml:lang="en"><a id="id4782018"></a><h2>Parameters</h2><div class="variablelist"><dl><dt><span class="term"><em class="parameter"><code>tess</code></em></span></dt><dd><p>
                    Specifies the tessellation object (created with <a href="gluNewTess.xml&#10;"><span class="citerefentry"><span class="refentrytitle">gluNewTess</span></span></a>).
                </p></dd></dl></div></div><div class="refsect1" lang="en" xml:lang="en"><a id="id4781912"></a><h2>Description</h2><p>
            <code class="function">gluBeginPolygon</code> and <a href="gluEndPolygon.xml&#10;"><span class="citerefentry"><span class="refentrytitle">gluEndPolygon</span></span></a> delimit the definition of a
            nonconvex polygon.
            To define such a polygon, first call <code class="function">gluBeginPolygon</code>.
            Then define the contours of the polygon
            by calling 
            <a href="gluTessVertex.xml&#10;"><span class="citerefentry"><span class="refentrytitle">gluTessVertex</span></span></a> for each vertex
            and <a href="gluNextContour.xml&#10;"><span class="citerefentry"><span class="refentrytitle">gluNextContour</span></span></a> to start each new contour.
            Finally, call <a href="gluEndPolygon.xml&#10;"><span class="citerefentry"><span class="refentrytitle">gluEndPolygon</span></span></a>
            to signal the end of the definition.
            See the <a href="gluTessVertex.xml&#10;"><span class="citerefentry"><span class="refentrytitle">gluTessVertex</span></span></a> and 
            <a href="gluNextContour.xml&#10;"><span class="citerefentry"><span class="refentrytitle">gluNextContour</span></span></a> reference pages for more details.
        </p><p>
            Once <a href="gluEndPolygon.xml&#10;"><span class="citerefentry"><span class="refentrytitle">gluEndPolygon</span></span></a> is called, the polygon is tessellated, and the
            resulting triangles are described through callbacks.
            See <a href="gluTessCallback.xml&#10;"><span class="citerefentry"><span class="refentrytitle">gluTessCallback</span></span></a> for descriptions of the callback functions.
        </p></div><div class="refsect1" lang="en" xml:lang="en"><a id="id4768526"></a><h2>Notes</h2><p>
            This command is obsolete and is provided for backward compatibility
            only. Calls to <code class="function">gluBeginPolygon</code> are mapped to 
            <a href="gluTessBeginPolygon.xml&#10;"><span class="citerefentry"><span class="refentrytitle">gluTessBeginPolygon</span></span></a>
            followed by 
            <a href="gluTessBeginContour.xml&#10;"><span class="citerefentry"><span class="refentrytitle">gluTessBeginContour</span></span></a>. Calls to <a href="gluEndPolygon.xml&#10;"><span class="citerefentry"><span class="refentrytitle">gluEndPolygon</span></span></a> are mapped
            to <a href="gluTessEndContour.xml&#10;"><span class="citerefentry"><span class="refentrytitle">gluTessEndContour</span></span></a> followed by <a href="gluTessEndPolygon.xml&#10;"><span class="citerefentry"><span class="refentrytitle">gluTessEndPolygon</span></span></a>.
        </p></div><div class="refsect1" lang="en" xml:lang="en"><a id="id4768569"></a><h2>EXAMPLE</h2><p>
            A quadrilateral with a triangular hole in it can be described like this:
            </p><pre class="programlisting">
gluBeginPolygon(tobj);
   gluTessVertex(tobj, v1, v1);
   gluTessVertex(tobj, v2, v2);
   gluTessVertex(tobj, v3, v3);
   gluTessVertex(tobj, v4, v4);
gluNextContour(tobj, GLU_INTERIOR);
   gluTessVertex(tobj, v5, v5);
   gluTessVertex(tobj, v6, v6);
   gluTessVertex(tobj, v7, v7);
gluEndPolygon(tobj);
            </pre><p>
